Some reminders to help carry you through 2024. Seems like 2023 was challenging for many, but as we step into 2024 keep your head up and walk by faith. Here’s to new beginnings #fadedculture

This is what worked for me when starting my journey as a barber. Keep in mind I was in my early teens and didn’t have  big bills or obligations besides scraping money for little Caesars. So if you’re starting off it’s suggest you keep this a side hustle until it pays more than your original job. Hope it helps

1. Offer your services for free for first time customer. Have a long vision for this, if you’re serious about making this a career one free haircut won’t hurt. You can pay these social platforms to help boost your stuff and or you can just offer first one for free, regardless your paying for marketing. I have clients to this day that started as a 1st time free client and stuck with me for 10+ years. So under promise and over deliver!
2. Offer incentives to your current customers for bringing some one. Again best thing worked for me was offering the half off or a free haircut lol, sounds funny but in an industry where there’s a ton a competition you gotta make your offer hard to resist.
- But of course none of this will work if your skills are lacking so take the time to study & practice. You can also head over to YouTube and watch Fadedculture for full length tutorials…. Just saying🙏🏽🏴 #fadedculture
